This repository contains a Cisco Packet Tracer lab demonstrating inter-VLAN routing using a router-on-a-stick topology.

## Files
- `.pkt` file contains the full network topology and configuration.
- `.pdf` file explains the network design and topology in detail.

## Overview
This network demonstrates a simple VLAN-segmented LAN using VLANs 10 and 20. It consists of four PCs, two switches, and one router.

The switches are connected via a trunk link on the Fa0/1 interfaces to allow VLAN traffic to pass between them. 

The router is configured using a router-on-a-stick topology to enable inter-VLAN routing between VLAN 10 and VLAN 20.
